modules.description: Provides operations to manage key-value stores with time-based versioning, including retrieving values, partial data, and metadata like size and last modification time. Works with `key` type from Mirage_kv and `Ptime.t` for timestamp handling. Used for atomic updates, data synchronization, and version-controlled storage in networked applications.

Provides operations to set, get, and delete key-value pairs in memory, with support for asynchronous Lwt operations. Works with string keys and byte sequence values. Useful for caching or temporary data storage in networked applications.

manages key-value stores with time-based versioning, enabling retrieval of values, partial data, and metadata such as size and last modification time. It supports atomic updates and data synchronization using `key` and `Ptime.t`. Operations include setting, removing, and querying versions of stored data. Examples include tracking changes in networked applications and restoring previous data states.
